Is there any interest in a human on anthro mouse consensual hypnosis story?

Short pitch: Human male is investigating embezzlement at a modern-day corporation. Discovers that one of the suspects is a friend from college, who was very sweet and kept her legs closed while burying herself in her studies. Her life was tightly monitored by her parents, who died shortly after she graduated college and left her nothing in their will.

His investigation quickly turns up that the culprit is computer error, but as part of the investigation he places several executives under hypnosis and records their questioning. The human's personal connection with the mouse is considered a benefit, since she will be more willing to divulge information if she does know anything. She doesn't, but during her trance he discovers that she's always had strong feelings for him. At the end of the trance, after turning off the recording, he plants the suggestion that she meet him after the investigation blows over.

She does. He wants her, both body and mind, but he wants her to ask for it. In college, she would play video games on his computer since her parents thought that "gaming PCs" were the work of the devil and forbid her from buying one. She told him back then that the only place she felt free was behind his locked door. He wants to hear that again, except this time he wants the mouse to feel free when she's entranced.

Haven't seen a lot of consensual hypnosis, so am not sure if there's an appetite for it. Couple of things that are worked for me:
Reality Checks ~hourly, things like trying to see with closed eyes, pinching yourself, trying to breath with closed mouth, looking at your fingers to see if they are wobbly/washed out
Simply focusing on your surroundings also helps. Looking for things that are out of place, eg. Dogs walking backwards, leaves falling upwards, missing sounds, anthros and shit like that
Writing a dream journal helps with remembering to your dreams, and makes it easier to notice when you are in a dream

There could be other good methods, but these are the ones I have tried, other suggestions are welcomed

Took around a month to get my first lucid dream, and after a year, I had at least one every week
